<HEADLINE>Star's wife Bonds with a new baby</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975224836</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BILL Wyman's wife Suzanne was so overcome with the excitement at the premiere
of the new Bond film GoldenEye that she went into labour.
The ex-Rolling Stone and his wife are now the proud parents of daughter Jessica
Rose, they announced yesterday.
``Most women find it pretty exciting just watching Pierce Brosnan and obviously
Suzanne is no exception,'' their spokeswoman said.
Suzanne Accosta, 35, started feeling contractions during the Royal premiere of
the film at the Odeon, Leicester Square on Tuesday evening, though she had not
expected to have her baby for another two days.
The Prince of Wales was in the audience, as were Brosnan, Tina Turner, and a
host of other stars.
Immediately the film finished, Bill, 57, and Suzanne rushed to hospital, and
Jessica was born at 3pm on Wednesday.
She weighed 6lb 5oz.
``Both mother and daughter are doing very well and Bill and Suzanne are very
happy and delighted,'' the spokeswoman said.
The couple already have one daughter, Katharine Noelle, aged 14 months, and
Bill has a grown-up son, Stephen, from a previous marriage.
</TEXT>
