<DATE>951124</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Sex case doctor out of jail</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975224839</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Phnom Penh, Thursday
BRITISH doctor Gavin Scott left a Phnom Penh prison today at the end of a
five-month jail term for sex attacks on five boys.
Scott stepped through the main gate with a lawyer and a British diplomat. When
asked about his health, he said: ``I'm still alive.''
On October 24, a court found Scott guilty of the attempted rape of five teenage
boys. He was fined and sentenced to two years in jail, with five months to be
served and the rest suspended.
Scott had been in custody for four months by the time of his trial, at which he
protested innocence.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
