<DATE>951124</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Pupil, 12, ill from drug pill</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975224861</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A SCHOOLBOY collapsed yesterday after taking a drug tablet he thought was a
sweet.
Ben Webb, 12, took the white pill, embossed with an A, from another pupil in
the dining hall at Hamble Secondary School, Southampton. Two hours later, he
collapsed with chest pains, unable to breath.
He was taken by ambulance to Southampton General Hospital but was sent home
later. Last night, police were questioning the other schoolboy to try to
discover what the pill contained.
</TEXT>
