<HEADLINE>Bundesbank seeks pledge</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>25</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975224929</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Frankfurt, Thursday - Bundesbank council member Guntram Palm said today nations
should make binding pledges that they will uphold fiscal austerity after having
joined the planned European Monetary Union.
``The Maastricht Treaty has no sufficient means to guard against individual
nations' unsolid fiscal policies,'' Mr Palm said, adding: ``This is the real
weak point in the agreement. This has to be improved in an appropriate way.''
</TEXT>
