American football
SCOTT Mitchell, playing on a sore right ankle, threw a career-best four
touchdown passes and shattered Bobby Layne's single-game team record with
410-yard yesterday as the Detroit Lions kept their play-off hopes alive with a
44-38 victory over the Minnesota Vikings.
Dallas, meanwhile, ended Kansas City's seven-game winning streak and a chance
to clinch a play-off berth but concern over Emmitt Smith's knee - he went down
without being tackled and the extent of the injury won't be known until today -
overshadowed the 24-12 victory, the Cowboys' tenth of the season.
Squash
WITH the top eight to qualify for the grand finals at the end of the season,
Scotland's Peter Nicol is lying seventh in the Hi-Tec Super Series rankings.
But the Scot is still struggling for form and went down to a surprise second
round defeat in the Pakistan Open yesterday. Nicol, seeded three, lost in five
games to Irishman Derek Ryan.
Athletics
