<HEADLINE>No-go Mysilv</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>42</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975224947</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CHAMPION Hurdle hope Mysilv will miss her intended engagement in the Bellway
Homes Fighting Fifth Hurdle at Newcastle tomorrow and will be aimed at the
Bonusphoto Bula Hurdle at Cheltenham on December 9.
Mysilv, the easy winner of a four-runner race at Cheltenham on her reappearance
and 12-1 with William Hill for the Champion, had been pencilled in to run at
Newcastle with Jimmy McCarthy, second jockey to Oliver Sherwood, a surprise
booking to partner her.
However, the mare's trainer Charlie Egerton said yesterday: ``Mysilv will not
run at New-    castle as I was not happy with her blood this morning and her
coat doesn't look as well as it normally does.
``One or two of my horses are giving a little cough but it is nothing serious,
and probably down to the weather.''
</TEXT>
